Introduction

This the an API doc for the JustBnb project (SPA)

Base URL: http://laravel-vue-spa.test

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Authentication JWT

Routes for managing the authentication/registration of the user

Login

Authenticate the user to the system

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/login" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"mhuels@example.org\",
    \"password\": \"PMA+\\/>Av)n=ds.mQ..`\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/login"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "mhuels@example.org",
    "password": "PMA+\/>Av)n=ds.mQ..`"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Headers

Example: application/json

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

Must be a valid email address. Example: mhuels@example.org

password   string   

Example: `PMA+/>Av)n=ds.mQ..``

Register

Register new user to the system

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/register" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"name\": \"odtpjbckzovsrfibuk\",
    \"email\": \"rosendo92@example.org\",
    \"password\": \"j;]H$i>5dl\\\\+`ar<S\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/register"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "name": "odtpjbckzovsrfibuk",
    "email": "rosendo92@example.org",
    "password": "j;]H$i>5dl\\+`ar<S"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):

Request      

POST api/register

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

name   string   

Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: odtpjbckzovsrfibuk

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Must not be greater than 255 characters. Example: rosendo92@example.org

password   string   

Must be at least 6 characters. Example: j;]H$i>5dl\+ar<S`

Logout

Logout authenticated user

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/logout" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "Authorization:: Bearer your_token"
const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/logout"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
    "Authorization:": "Bearer your_token",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "status": "success",
    "message": "Successfully logged out"
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST api/logout

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Authorization:      

Example: Bearer your_token

);

    "Accept": "application/json",

};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",

Basket

checkout

Handle the checkout action request.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/checkout" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --header "Authorization:: Bearer your_token" \
    --data "{
    \"bookings\": [
        {
            \"bookable_id\": \"voluptatem\",
            \"from\": \"2084-02-15\",
            \"to\": \"2050-04-15\"
        }
    ],
    \"customer\": {
        \"first_name\": \"tkigdmrddopxfeboltxssrlvacnnmfwgecuuicgtjpdxzq\",
        \"last_name\": \"vrgwlclqanosszsn\",
        \"street\": \"brrycsnwinxyhjdlrlkoth\",
        \"city\": \"hjxhgkkaswqqhudffgbdpbhlovmrlsbfm\",
        \"email\": \"heaney.angela@example.net\",
        \"country\": \"hvztlqvntwphnnjwgbzgezuwaglphfuprsjzqggoesryutxbostyeqyqwotyxizig\",
        \"state\": \"qo\",
        \"zip\": \"qocmxwxnbdrliuhfpyasewslajlrlcfpxdwdaptmrwddrakagvlsglmwnjqexfxebhjqxvjocmzaupthuexztac\"
    }
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/checkout"

const headers = {

            "to": "2050-04-15"
        }
    ],

Request      

POST api/checkout

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Authorization:      

Example: Bearer your_token

Body Parameters

bookings   object[]  optional  
bookable_id   string   

Example: voluptatem

from   string   

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after or equal to today. Example: 2084-02-15

to   string   

Must be a valid date. Must be a date after or equal to bookings.*.from. Example: 2050-04-15

customer   object  optional  
first_name   string   

Must be at least 2 characters. Example: tkigdmrddopxfeboltxssrlvacnnmfwgecuuicgtjpdxzq

last_name   string   

Must be at least 2 characters. Example: vrgwlclqanosszsn

street   string   

Must be at least 3 characters. Example: brrycsnwinxyhjdlrlkoth

city   string   

Must be at least 3 characters. Example: hjxhgkkaswqqhudffgbdpbhlovmrlsbfm

email   string   

Must be a valid email address. Example: heaney.angela@example.net

country   string   

Must be at least 2 characters. Example: hvztlqvntwphnnjwgbzgezuwaglphfuprsjzqggoesryutxbostyeqyqwotyxizig

state   string   

Must be at least 2 characters. Example: qo

zip   string   

Must be at least 2 characters. Example: qocmxwxnbdrliuhfpyasewslajlrlcfpxdwdaptmrwddrakagvlsglmwnjqexfxebhjqxvjocmzaupthuexztac

Bookable

Routes for managing the bookable resource

Index

Display a listing of all Bookings.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/bookables" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://laravel-vue-spa.test/api/bookables"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
